@startuml
title  End-to-End Scan Flow

actor User as U
participant "Next.js" as FE
participant "C# API" as API
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Redis" as Redis
participant "Java Worker" as Worker
participant "External" as Ext

== Phase 1: Setup ==
U -> FE: 1. Sign up / Log in
FE -> API: 2. Auth request
API -> DB: 3. Create user
U -> FE: 4. Add domain
FE -> API: 5. POST /domains
API -> DB: 6. Store domain with token
U -> FE: 7. Add DNS TXT record
U -> FE: 8. Click verify
FE -> API: 9. POST /verify
API -> Ext: 10. Check DNS
API -> DB: 11. Mark verified

== Phase 2: Scan ==
U -> FE: 12. Click Run Scan
FE -> API: 13. POST /scans
API -> DB: 14. Create scan record
API -> Redis: 15. LPUSH scan:queue
API --> FE: 16. 202 Accepted

== Phase 3: Processing ==
Redis -> Worker: 17. BRPOP gets job
Worker -> DB: 18. Update status='processing'
Worker -> Ext: 19. 5 parallel scans
Worker -> Ext: 20. OpenAI API
Worker -> DB: 21. Store findings
Worker -> Redis: 22. Update status

== Phase 4: Results ==
FE -> API: 23. Poll GET /scans/{id}
API -> DB: 24. Query results
API --> FE: 25. Return findings
FE --> U: 26. Display dashboard

@enduml